# Crispy Tofu Fingers

Based on [easygfrecipes.com](https://easygfrecipes.com/crispy-tofu-fingers-recipe/)

{ rating="0" image="None" }
:::
:::

## Ingredients

- [ ] 12 oz extra-firm tofu
- [ ] 1 tsp vegetable oil
- [ ] 4 oz sweet and sour sauce or barbecue sauce
- [ ] Salt to taste
- [ ] Garlic powder, onion powder, smoked paprika, or cayenne pepper (optional)

## Recipe

1. Preheat oven to 400°F (200°C). Apply vegetable oil to a cookie sheet.
1. Slice tofu lengthwise into strips approximately 1/4 inch thick.
1. Wrap tofu strips in paper towels and press under a heavy object for at least 30 minutes to remove excess moisture.
1. Pour sauce into a shallow dish and coat each tofu strip thoroughly on all sides.
1. Arrange sauce-coated strips on the prepared sheet in a single layer without overlapping.
1. Season with salt and any desired seasonings.
1. Bake for 20-30 minutes until golden brown and crispy around the edges. Optionally broil for a final 1-2 minutes for extra crispness.
1. Cool briefly before serving.

## Notes

- Pressing is essential - the more moisture removed, the crispier the result; use a tofu press for best results
- Air fryer alternative: 375°F for 15-20 minutes, flipping halfway
- Store leftovers up to 3 days refrigerated; reheat in oven or air fryer to maintain texture
